race.comment: Very deep maiden. LETHAL LOVE (7) settled near the speed then fought on well to hold third last start over this course and distance. Drawn a little awkwardly but with even luck she can break through at start three. SEMIBREVE (2) is one of many dangers. Came with a powerful burst to get up for second last time out when resuming at this track and distance. Progressive mare who will be hard to hold out. VIRGIL'S GIFT (10) is a $300k Street Boss filly on debut for the powerful Waterhouse & Bott stable. Her latest trial at Randwick was very impressive and she's a half-sister to the Group performed Celestial Bling. Looks well placed and can score a debut win. LA BASILIQUE (6) looks another who can start her career on a positive note. Purchased for a million bucks, this Waller and Yulong filly ticks a few boxes on debut and is worth keeping an eye on.
